An Ansible ad hoc command uses the /usr/bin/ansible command-line tool to automate 
a single task on one or more managed nodes. ad hoc commands are quick and easy, but they are not reusable. S
o why learn about ad hoc commands? ad hoc commands demonstrate the simplicity and power of Ansible. The concepts you
learn here will port over directly to the playbook language. Before reading and executing these examples, please read How to build your inventory.

